<TITLE> BFF stay quiet on BNS issue </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnews24.com)  There was no reaction from the Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) after the Bangladesh Cricket Board desired to hold the 2011 ICC World Cup matches at the Bangabandhu National Stadium. The BCB board of directors in its meeting on Sunday took a unanimous decision that they would officially place a proposal to the state minister for youth and sports on holding a couple of World Cup matches at the BNS. When the BFF president Kazi Salahuddin's attention was drawn to the BCB's proposal, the BFF boss declined to say anything. "No comment, I will only make comments if it is needed." It is decided that the BNS will host the opening ceremony of the cricket extravaganza while the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium in Mirpur and Narayangnaj Fatullah Cricket Stadium will host the eight matches. However, the BFF vice-president Badal Roy said they will sit in a meeting soon as well as meet the Prime Minister if it is needed. bd
